message: I HATE it when there are no good movies out. All the good ones get released at the end the year, and then it's a void.
Can this movie possibly be as good as this trailer? http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DlYYreuK8vo
The only Terrence Malick I've seen was The Thin Red Line... It was...interesting.

Annelfo: The Housemaid is out now in New York at least, and it's excellent. There's also 127 Hours, The Fighter, and Mike Leigh's "Another Year", which are all supposed to be very good. "No Strings Attached" was really funny and well-acted as well.
